#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:8
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:10
msgid ""
"This page contains answers to frequently asked questions about Spack. If you "
"have questions that are not answered here, feel free to ask on `Slack "
"<https://slack.spack.io>`_ or `GitHub Discussions <https://github.com/spack/"
"spack/discussions>`_. If you've learned the answer to a question that you "
"think should be here, please consider contributing to this page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:21
msgid "Why does Spack pick particular versions and variants?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:23
msgid "This question comes up in a variety of forms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:25
msgid ""
"Why does Spack seem to ignore my package preferences from ``packages.yaml`` "
"config?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:26
msgid ""
"Why does Spack toggle a variant instead of using the default from the "
"``package.py`` file?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:28
msgid ""
"The short answer is that Spack always picks an optimal configuration based "
"on a complex set of criteria\\ [#f1]_. These criteria are more nuanced than "
"always choosing the latest versions or default variants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:34
msgid ""
"As a rule of thumb: requirements + constraints > reuse > preferences > "
"defaults."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:36
msgid ""
"The following set of criteria (from lowest to highest precedence) explain "
"common cases where concretization output may seem surprising at first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:39
msgid ""
":ref:`Package preferences <package-preferences>` configured in ``packages."
"yaml`` override variant defaults from ``package.py`` files, and influence "
"the optimal ordering of versions. Preferences are specified as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:43
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  foo:\n"
"    version: [1.0, 1.1]\n"
"    variants: ~mpi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:50
msgid ""
":ref:`Reuse concretization <concretizer-options>` configured in "
"``concretizer.yaml`` overrides preferences, since it's typically faster to "
"reuse an existing spec than to build a preferred one from sources. When "
"build caches are enabled, specs may be reused from a remote location too. "
"Reuse concretization is configured as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:55
msgid ""
"concretizer:\n"
"  reuse: dependencies  # other options are 'true' and 'false'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:60
msgid ""
":ref:`Package requirements <package-requirements>` configured in ``packages."
"yaml``, and constraints from the command line as well as ``package.py`` "
"files override all of the above. Requirements are specified as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:64
msgid ""
"packages:\n"
"  foo:\n"
"    require:\n"
"    - \"@1.2: +mpi\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:71
msgid ""
"Requirements and constraints restrict the set of possible solutions, while "
"reuse behavior and preferences influence what an optimal solution looks like."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:76
msgid "Footnotes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../frequently_asked_questions.rst:77
msgid ""
"The exact list of criteria can be retrieved with the ``spack solve`` command"
msgstr ""
